# Memory System Rules

- All memory access goes through `MemoryManager` in `memory/manager.py`
- Never access individual tiers directly from agents
- Schema changes require a migration script in `scripts/migrations/NNN_description.py`
- Use `aiosqlite` for all SQLite operations (no sync sqlite3)
- Every interaction (user/assistant turn) is immediately persisted to `data/interactions.db`
- Qdrant operations use the async client
- 5 tiers: Sensory Buffer → Working → Episodic → Semantic → Procedural
- Working memory is token-budgeted and priority-queued
